HEADWORD: Albertype
<hw>Al"ber*type</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧l"b⟦etil⟧r*t⟦imac⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From the name of the inventor, <etsep>Albert</etsep>, of
Munich.]</ety> <def>A picture printed from a kind of gelatine plate
produced by means of a photographic negative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

